rComments: Her lectures are fast-paced and hard to follow and her tests were hard. She mentioned that her tests are fair and straightforward if you attended classes and studied, I studied a week straight for both tests and not only didn't do well, but I didn't even recognize some of the questions. All test-based except for one group project worth 15%.

Kristi is a great prof, I took APA2180 and APA2312 with her and I enjoyed it! She makes sure you understand the content and repeats stuff many times. Cares about her students. Make sure to attend to get a better understanding.

Course is about research, so people have different opinions on how they enjoy the course. As someone who doesn't see research as a first choice, but something just to try out in university. Gave great feedback throughout items if you asked, and was accessible for group meetings/individual questions. Is test heavy though for the midterm and final.

I enjoyed this class, the prof teaches with passion and wants you to get good marks. Expectations are clear and she repeates the important stuff many times. Before starting new material she reviews the important info from the class before, which was very helpful. Quizzes helped to stay on track. Study from the slides no need for the book.

I did not find this class very interesting. You have 2 exams (a midterm and final), a group project, and weekly quizzes. Her exams were very limited to time considering how many questions she gives, I found I was very rushed and would miss questions at the end. The research project was fairly long so make sure you dont leave it to the last minute.

She is an okay prof. I agree with other comments that she comes off as rude in emails and other forms of communication. Ive been taken aback by the way she communicates as times. But other than that she explains the material well and you can tell how passionate she is about research. Midterms aren't too difficult if you pay attention.

She is extremely rude in her emails.  Kind of belittles you and makes you feel stupid for asking questions. Do not take her if you don't have to. I don't know if she means to come off that way but she does. Her responses made me not ask her any more questions because I simply felt stupid.

Hands down the rudest prof I have ever come into contact with. It's super clear she is only in this profession to do research, she doesn't care about her students. Don't bother asking questions unless you're okay with condescending responses that belittle your intelligence. If you can avoid her you 10/10 should.
